### Grammar Mistakes (Tense and Agreement Issues)
1. **"So there's a running story about Andreessen Horowitz basically saying people in big tech companies are not doing enough real work to justify their existence..."**
   - **Issue:** "there's" should be "there is" for formal writing.
   - **Correction:** "So there is a running story about Andreessen Horowitz basically saying people in big tech companies are not doing enough real work to justify their existence..."

2. **"And while this might seem to an unwarranted assault on the work ethic of tech workers (who I'm sure are mostly diligent and hardworking), I can't help but agree that he's probably onto something, at least from the capitalist perspective."**
   - **Issue:** "might seem to an unwarranted assault" should be "might seem an unwarranted assault."
   - **Correction:** "And while this might seem an unwarranted assault on the work ethic of tech workers (who I'm sure are mostly diligent and hardworking), I can't help but agree that he's probably onto something, at least from the capitalist perspective."

3. **"In fact, back when tech stocks were down last year, I briefly wondered whether it would be a good idea to buy some at the relatively low prices -- in particular META and GOOG."**
   - **Issue:** "were down last year" should be "were down in the past year" for clarity.
   - **Correction:** "In fact, back when tech stocks were down in the past year, I briefly wondered whether it would be a good idea to buy some at the relatively low prices -- in particular META and GOOG."

4. **"That, and when shareholders are unhappy, they can always layoff more people to reduce costs and increase margins and profit, and I had no ounce of doubt that they can cut costs by almost half without really affecting day to day operations."**
   - **Issue:** "layoff" should be "lay off."
   - **Correction:** "That, and when shareholders are unhappy, they can always lay off more people to reduce costs and increase margins and profit, and I had no ounce of doubt that they can cut costs by almost half without really affecting day-to-day operations."

5. **"In the end I didn't make any trades, if only because I would have hated how I participated and enabled this kind of predatory capitalist attitude -- but ideological concerns aside, the logic is solid."**
   - **Issue:** "I would have hated how I participated" should be "I would have hated participating."
   - **Correction:** "In the end I didn't make any trades, if only because I would have hated participating and enabling this kind of predatory capitalist attitude -- but ideological concerns aside, the logic is solid."

### Serious Stylistic Issues
1. **"So there's a running story about Andreessen Horowitz basically saying people in big tech companies are not doing enough real work to justify their existence..."**
   - **Issue:** The sentence is informal and lacks clarity.
   - **Correction:** "There is a running story about Andreessen Horowitz claiming that people in big tech companies are not doing enough real work to justify their existence."

2. **"And while this might seem an unwarranted assault on the work ethic of tech workers (who I'm sure are mostly diligent and hardworking), I can't help but agree that he's probably onto something, at least from the capitalist perspective."**
   - **Issue:** The sentence is overly long and convoluted.
   - **Correction:** "While this might seem like an unwarranted assault on the work ethic of tech workers (who are mostly diligent and hardworking), I can't help but agree that he has a point, at least from a capitalist perspective."

3. **"In fact, back when tech stocks were down in the past year, I briefly wondered whether it would be a good idea to buy some at the relatively low prices -- in particular META and GOOG."**
   - **Issue:** The sentence is too long and could be split for clarity.
   - **Correction:** "In fact, when tech stocks were down in the past year, I briefly considered buying some at the relatively low prices, particularly META and GOOG."

4. **"That, and when shareholders are unhappy, they can always lay off more people to reduce costs and increase margins and profit, and I had no ounce of doubt that they can cut costs by almost half without really affecting day-to-day operations."**
   - **Issue:** The sentence is overly long and complex.
   - **Correction:** "Additionally, when shareholders are unhappy, companies can always lay off more people to reduce costs and increase margins and profit. I had no doubt that they could cut costs by almost half without significantly affecting day-to-day operations."

5. **"In the end I didn't make any trades, if only because I would have hated participating and enabling this kind of predatory capitalist attitude -- but ideological concerns aside, the logic is solid."**
   - **Issue:** The sentence is too long and could be split for clarity.
   - **Correction:** "In the end, I didn't make any trades, primarily because I would have hated participating in and enabling this kind of predatory capitalist attitude. However, ideological concerns aside, the logic is solid."

